[SN]TITLE[SN]
Hinterland actor 'assaulted' outside Aberystwyth bar

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An actor who plays a police officer in the BBC Wales drama Hinterland has been allegedly assaulted outside a bar in Ceredigion.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Aneirin Hughes was allegedly attacked outside Rummers Wine Bar in Aberystwyth at about 00:45 BST on Sunday morning.
The 58-year-old, who plays Chf Supt Brian Prosser in the bilingual drama, suffered minor facial injuries.
A 21-year-old man was arrested on suspicion of assault and bailed by police, pending further inquiries.
